  "prompt": "What facts about the United States do foreigners not believe until they come to America?",
  "response": "Here are some common experiences foreigners find surprising about the United States:\n\n1. How large and spread out everything is\n- Vast distances between cities\n- Large portion sizes\n- Huge parking lots and wide roads\n\n2. Customer service differences\n- Very friendly and enthusiastic service\n- Tipping culture being mandatory\n- Employees being overly cheerful\n\n3. Pricing oddities\n- Prices not including sales tax\n- Different prices in different states\n- Cheap gas and alcohol compared to many countries\n\n4. Cultural quirks\n- How casual Americans dress\n- Air conditioning everywhere\n- Drive-through services for everything\n- Patriotism and flag displays\n- Gun ownership prevalence\n\n5. Food and drink\n- Extremely sweet foods\n- Massive soft drink portions\n- Variety of processed and packaged foods\n- Free refills on drinks\n\n6. Transportation\n- Car-dependent culture\n- Limited public transportation\n- Size of personal vehicles\n- Lack of pedestrian-friendly infrastructure\n\n7. Healthcare and education costs\n- Extremely high medical expenses\n- Student loan debt\n- Complex health insurance system\n\n8. Work culture\n- Limited vacation time\n- Work-centric lifestyle\n- Less formal workplace environments\n\nThese perceptions can vary based on individual experiences and backgrounds.",
